  "title": "Sysmon DNS Tunneling via Network Connection",
  "description": "Detects suspicious processes making DNS connections (port 53) that could indicate DNS tunneling for data exfiltration or C2 communication.\n",
  "query": "('Log Source' = 'Windows Sysmon Events' or 'Log Source' = 'Windows Sysmon Operational Logs' or 'Log Source' = 'SOC Sysmon Network Logs' or 'Log Source' = 'SOC Windows Sysmon Logs') and (('Destination Port' = 53 and Initiated = 'true') and (('Process Name' like '*\\\\powershell.exe' or 'Process Name' like '*\\\\cmd.exe' or 'Process Name' like '*\\\\nslookup.exe' or 'Process Name' like '*\\\\iodine.exe' or 'Process Name' like '*\\\\dnscat2.exe' or 'Process Name' like '*\\\\dns2tcp.exe')) and not (('Process Name' like '*\\\\svchost.exe' or 'Process Name' like '*\\\\dns.exe')))",
